cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SD

This paper uses natural language processing (NLP) techniques to analyze online propaganda targeting women by ISIS and a Catholic forum. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and its applications. The paper also involves sentiment analysis, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper deals with cybersecurity and counterterrorism, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper involves data mining and analysis, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering).
